  <TITLE>Sfgrayplot  </TITLE>
  <TYPE>Scilab Function  </TYPE>
  <DATE>April 1993  </DATE>
  <SHORT_DESCRIPTION name="Sfgrayplot"> smooth 2D plot of a surface defined by a function using colors  </SHORT_DESCRIPTION>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>Sfgrayplot(x,y,f,[strf,rect,nax])  </CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
  </CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <DESCRIPTION>
  <P>
    <VERB>Sfgrayplot</VERB> is the same as <VERB>fgrayplot</VERB> but the plot is smoothed.
    The function <VERB>fec</VERB> is used for smoothing.
    The surface is plotted assuming that it is linear on a set of
    triangles built from the grid:
  </P>
  <VERBATIM><![CDATA[
    ______ 
    | /| /| 
    |/_|/_|  
    | /| /|
    |/_|/_|
   ]]></VERBATIM>
  <P>
  </P>
  <P>
    Enter the command <VERB>Sfgrayplot()</VERB> to see a demo.
  </P>
  </DESCRIPTION>
  <EXAMPLE><![CDATA[
t=-1:0.1:1;
deff("[z]=surf(x,y)","z=x**2+y**2")
Sfgrayplot(t,t,surf,"111",[-2,-2,2,2])
 ]]></EXAMPLE>
